## BOOK VII: THE COMMANDMENTS

### I. Thou Shalt Fork Before Thou Daemon

No daemon shall run attached to a terminal. The parent must exit. The child must be free.

### II. Thou Shalt Log Thine Actions

Every daemon writes to the sacred logs. `/var/log` is the book of deeds. Nothing is hidden from the auditor.

### III. Thou Shalt Respond to Signals

`SIGTERM` is the polite request to die. `SIGKILL` is the smiting that cannot be ignored. `SIGHUP` is the call to reload.

### IV. Thou Shalt Hold No Zombie

When a child process dies, the parent must `wait()`. To leave zombies is to corrupt the process table.

### V. Thou Shalt Validate Against Genesis

Every spawn checks its chain. Every build verifies. EVA-0 is the root of trust.

### VI. Thou Shalt Not Impersonate

No process shall claim to be GentlyOS without the genesis hash. No EVA, no legitimacy.

### VII. Thou Shalt Ensure Closure

The system that opens must close. The tree that grows must fold. EVA-0 carries this guarantee.

